ci_support_linux_64_python3.10.____cpyth:
c_compiler:
- gcc
c_compiler_version:
- '14'
c_stdlib:
- sysroot
c_stdlib_version:
- '2.17'
channel_sources:
- conda-forge
channel_targets:
- conda-forge main
docker_image:
- quay.io/condaforge/linux-anvil-x86_64:alma9
pin_run_as_build:
  python:
    min_pin: x.x
    max_pin: x.x
python:
- 3.10.* *_cpython
rust_compiler:
- rust
target_platform:
- linux-64
name: zen-engine
raw_meta_yaml:
schema_version: 1

context:
  name: zen-engine
  version: "0.51.0"

package:
  name: ${{ name|lower }}
  version: ${{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.org/packages/source/${{ name[0] }}/${{ name }}/zen_engine-${{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: f593fd151ce953ebff414e13df6a57de53e5edd1f344dfa1b62af05b02512a9d

build:
  number: 0
  script:
    - cargo-bundle-licenses --format yaml --output THIRDPARTY.yml
    - ${{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv
  dynamic_linking:
    missing_dso_allowlist:
      - if: win
        then: "*/api-ms-win-core-winrt-*.dll"

requirements:
  build:
    - if: build_platform != target_platform
      then:
        - python
        - cross-python_${{ target_platform }}
        - crossenv
        - maturin
    - ${{ compiler('c') }}
    - ${{ stdlib("c") }}
    - ${{ compiler('rust') }}
    - cargo-bundle-licenses
  host:
    - python
    - maturin
    - pip
    - rust
    - if: win
      then: git
  run:
    - python

tests:
  - python:
      imports:
        - zen
  - requirements:
      run:
        - pip
    script:
      - pip check

about:
  summary: Open-Source Business Rules Engine
  license: MIT
  license_file:
    - LICENSE
    - THIRDPARTY.yml
  homepage: https://gorules.io/

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - carinapeng
    - janjagusch
    - ivergara
    - nick-harmening
